04/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey--Pirates attacked a Turkish commercial ship off the coast of Nigeria, in western Africa, on Monday (August 3rd), injuring two of the 22 crew members. According to NTV, the vessel was transporting rice. In the past, pirates have repeatedly attacked commercial vessels across the continent, in the Gulf of Aden, off the Somali coast, in eastern Africa. Two Turkish frigates are patrolling the region as part of a NATO force there. (DHA, NTV, RIA Novosti - 03/08/09) 
